Elytra: Humeri more or less widely rounded at apices, without denticles. Additional ninth stria not separated from lateral furrow by convexity. Basal pore present. Each third interval with several (
3–9
) discal pores. Each fifth and seventh intervals without discal pores, or, discal pores, if present, hardly recognizable against backgrounds of general puncturation. Series umbilicate irregular, without a distinct gap medially.

Male genitalia: Median lobe of aedeagus (
Figs 7–14
) arcuate, with rather short terminal lamella, more or less strongly bent dorsad at apex; ventral surface of median lobe unbordered. Apical orifice in dorsal position, extending basally and covered by more strongly sclerotized plica at apex. Internal sac without any distinct sclerotized structures.
